menu "breadboard: bb_http_client"

config BB_HTTP_CLIENT_KEEPALIVE
    bool "Enable TCP/TLS keep-alive on reusable sessions"
    default y
    help
        When enabled, bb_http_client_session_open sets keep_alive_enable=true
        on the underlying esp_http_client so the TCP/TLS connection is reused
        across bb_http_client_session_post calls (lower latency per publish).
        Disable to open+close a fresh connection on every session_post call
        (higher latency, no idle-socket wedge risk).  The default (y) preserves
        the behaviour prior to B1-284.

config BB_HTTP_CLIENT_BACKOFF_BASE_MS
    int "Retry backoff base interval (ms)"
    default 2000
    range 100 30000
    help
        Base delay for the exponential back-off ladder used between transport
        retry attempts in bb_http_client_get and bb_http_client_post. The
        ladder is computed as: attempt 0 → base, attempt 1 → base*2, attempt
        2 → min(base*4, max). Default 2000 ms matches the prior hardcoded
        value (no behavior change).

config BB_HTTP_CLIENT_BACKOFF_MAX_MS
    int "Retry backoff maximum interval (ms)"
    default 8000
    range 500 120000
    help
        Cap on the exponential back-off ladder. Derived ladder entries beyond
        this value are clamped to this maximum. Default 8000 ms matches the
        prior hardcoded maximum (no behavior change).

config BB_HTTP_CLIENT_STREAM_CHUNK_BYTES
    int "Streaming GET chunk buffer size (bytes)"
    default 2048
    range 256 8192
    help
        Size of the stack-allocated chunk buffer used by
        bb_http_client_get_stream to feed response bytes to the caller's
        callback. Larger values reduce callback frequency at the cost of
        stack space. Default 2048 matches the prior hardcoded value (no
        behavior change).

config BB_HTTP_CLIENT_DEFAULT_BUF_SIZE
    int "Default esp_http_client internal receive buffer size (bytes)"
    default 4096
    range 512 16384
    help
        Default value for cfg.buffer_size passed to esp_http_client. Controls
        the internal HTTP receive buffer. Increase for servers that send large
        response headers. Default 4096 matches the prior hardcoded fallback
        (no behavior change).

config BB_HTTP_CLIENT_DEFAULT_TIMEOUT_MS
    int "Default request timeout (ms)"
    default 10000
    range 1000 120000
    help
        Default per-request timeout for bb_http_client_get when cfg.timeout_ms
        is 0.

config BB_HTTP_CLIENT_DEFAULT_MAX_ATTEMPTS
    int "Default retry attempts"
    default 3
    range 1 10
    help
        Default number of transport attempts before giving up.

config BB_HTTP_CLIENT_TASK_STACK_SIZE
    int "Minimum task stack size for callers of bb_http_client_get* (bytes)"
    default 8192
    range 4096 16384
    help
        Any FreeRTOS task that calls bb_http_client_get or
        bb_http_client_get_stream must allocate at least this much stack to
        cover the mbedTLS handshake + cert-bundle parse path. 8 KiB is the
        empirically-validated floor on ESP32-S3; 4 KiB overflows into adjacent
        heap. Use the BB_HTTP_CLIENT_TASK_STACK macro from bb_http_client.h
        when calling xTaskCreate so the budget stays consistent across
        consumers.

        NOTE (B1-274): this default is intentionally NOT gate-keyed on
        BB_HTTP_TLS_ENABLE / BB_MQTT_TLS_ENABLE.  The OTA/update-check HTTPS
        path (esp_http_client + crt-bundle via bb_ota_check / bb_ota_pull)
        is always compiled in regardless of the sink TLS gates and requires
        >= 8 KiB of task stack for the GitHub TLS handshake.  Lowering this
        below 8192 on any build that includes bb_ota_check or bb_ota_pull
        risks a stack overflow at update-check time even when the sink TLS
        gates are OFF.  Keep at 8192 unless you have explicitly excluded both
        update-check and OTA-pull from your build.

        Note: the TLS handshake also requires a contiguous internal heap block
        of roughly CONFIG_MBEDTLS_SSL_IN_CONTENT_LEN bytes at handshake time.
        On no-PSRAM pull-strategy boards, bb_ota_pull's pre-flight guard
        (CONFIG_BB_TLS_HEAP_CONTIGUOUS_FLOOR) enforces this at runtime.

endmenu
